
 JSLint plugin for jEdit
 ================================ = = =  -  -

 INSTALL

   1. Download Rhino (JavaScript Engine for Java)
        http://www.mozilla.org/rhino/download.html

   2. Place the "js.jar", from the Rhino release zip in the same folder
      as the other jEdit plugins.
        e.g. cd %USERPROFILE%\.jedit\jars

   3. Copy the "JSLint.jar", from this relese in the same folder as the
      other jEdit plugins.
        e.g. cd %USERPROFILE%\.jedit\jars
		
   4. Open jEdit -> Plugins -> Plugin Manager...
      there you need to check, both jar files (js.jar and JSLint.jar)

   5. Open jEdit -> Plugins -> Plugin Options... -> JSLint
      change some settings, if you like...


